1
00:00:10,272 --> 00:00:11,584
(Sun Honglei)

2
00:00:11,923 --> 00:00:12,992
(Li Naiwen)

3
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,416
(Guo Jingfei)

4
00:00:17,115 --> 00:00:18,912
(Liu Yuning)

5
00:00:19,264 --> 00:00:21,024
(Gong Jun)

6
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:23,072
(Chen Xingxu)

7
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:26,272
(Wang Yuwen)

8
00:00:26,656 --> 00:00:28,829
(Lin Yi)

9
00:00:31,882 --> 00:00:34,496
=Wow The World S2 Extra Episode=

10
00:00:34,592 --> 00:00:35,552
(Kiss the Shark Overtime)
Come on, everyone.

11
00:00:35,872 --> 00:00:38,672
Tonight, let's review an old game.

12
00:00:38,672 --> 00:00:41,352
This game is called Kiss the Shark.

13
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:42,976
The rules are very simple.

14
00:00:42,976 --> 00:00:44,512
(Everyone wears headphones)
We do whisper-down-the-lane

15
00:00:44,512 --> 00:00:45,120
(First person relays the exact melody)
and passes on

16
00:00:45,232 --> 00:00:46,784
(The others relay the previous melody)
the music they hear in the headphones

17
00:00:46,784 --> 00:00:47,648
(The last person guesses the melody)
to the next person.

18
00:00:47,648 --> 00:00:48,512
(Say the song title to succeed)
When passing it on,

19
00:00:48,512 --> 00:00:50,352
headphones will play distracting music.

20
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:52,600
Under the distraction, you need to

21
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,840
take the melody sung by the previous one

22
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:56,200
and pass it to the next person.

23
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,360
The last member one the melody

24
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,880
and says the song title.

25
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:00,920
That means the challenge is successful.

26
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:03,120
We're now starting an extra round.

27
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,760
Play one we all know if you dare.

28
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:08,400
(Seconded)
Yeah.

29
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,840
(Seconded)
Play something we've all heard.

30
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,928
If after listening to it, we all say,

31
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:14,000
(Seconded)
"Oh, it's that song."

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:14,680
Then we'll admit defeat.

33
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,800
Come on, give us one everyone has heard.

34
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:17,200
Yeah.

35
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,160
Okay.

36
00:01:19,424 --> 00:01:20,480
Come on, same order.

37
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,440
(I believe we can do it)
I refuse to believe we might lose.

38
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:24,672
(Lacking confidence)

39
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,304
(I don't think that'll work)

40
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,760
Let's strategize a bit.

41
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,040
Okay?

42
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,640
(Give us some room to improve)
Feels like we might actually succeed.

43
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,920
Okay?

44
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:34,120
This time, let's start with Honglei.

45
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,640
If we're going down,
we're going down together.

46
00:01:37,088 --> 00:01:38,848
(You rascal)

47
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,160
Then Honglei goes first, okay?

48
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:42,200
Honglei is good at guessing melodies.

49
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,320
No problem.

50
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:44,760
(High hopes)
Okay.

51
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:45,480
Okay, second.

52
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,320
Gong Jun, okay?

53
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,440
Alright.

54
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,560
Who wants to be the third?

55
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,560
Who wants to take over from Gong Jun?

56
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,480
I'll be the third, then...

57
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,160
- Lin Yi, you take it.
- I'll do it.

58
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:52,704
I'll do it.

59
00:01:52,704 --> 00:01:53,216
Okay.

60
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,400
Who's after you?

61
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:55,440
Yuwen, you go.

62
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,520
I'm duty-bound.

63
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,800
I remember the tune clearly.

64
00:01:59,364 --> 00:02:00,640
(Relieved)

65
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,320
After Yuwen,

66
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:01,800
Fei.

67
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:02,320
Okay.

68
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,320
I'll take over from Fei.

69
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,000
Alright.

70
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,880
Then I'll take over from you.

71
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:06,160
You take over from me.

72
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,080
I'll be last.

73
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,880
You're the last one.

74
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,400
I'm the last one again?

75
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,440
(Worried)

76
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,000
Can you be the last one, bro?

77
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,080
Sure.

78
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,032
But you know all the song titles.

79
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,240
Alright, then I'll be last.

80
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:17,680
You're last.

81
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,360
I'm last, okay.

82
00:02:20,407 --> 00:02:21,344
(The last two swap places)

83
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,640
Yeah, Yuning is last.

84
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,400
Well,

85
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,640
(Might not really know the song)
by the end, I basically can't guess it,

86
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,000
I think.

87
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,080
(Confident)
That's impossible.

88
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,120
No way.

89
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,600
(Being certain)
Absolutely impossible.

90
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,320
Yuning is last.

91
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,600
(I'm relieved)

92
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,008
(Giving advice)
Honglei, if you realize

93
00:02:39,008 --> 00:02:39,960
you don't know the song,

94
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,520
ask them to change it immediately.

95
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,120
I'll definitely do that.

96
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,680
That way, it's foolproof.

97
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,048
Right.

98
00:02:46,715 --> 00:02:49,312
(Passing direction, First relay)

99
00:02:54,976 --> 00:02:59,560
(Playing the music)

100
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,120
Honglei.

101
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,440
Is this song okay?

102
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,936
Is it the song playing in my headphones?

103
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:04,960
Yes.

104
00:03:05,344 --> 00:03:07,776
(Will everyone know this song?)

105
00:03:08,416 --> 00:03:09,504
(Anticipating)

106
00:03:10,496 --> 00:03:11,296
(Curious)

107
00:03:11,512 --> 00:03:13,664
(Identifying the song)

108
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:16,680
Are you sure?

109
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,080
I've heard it.

110
00:03:18,592 --> 00:03:19,360
(It's in the bag)

111
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,280
It's very familiar.

112
00:03:21,536 --> 00:03:23,328
(Will I be familiar with it?)

113
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,408
(Come on, Jun)

114
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,512
(Nervous)

115
00:03:28,768 --> 00:03:32,064
(Watch me)

116
00:03:32,064 --> 00:03:32,720
(Pass the song The Flower Guardian)

117
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:35,800
♪You can understand my rainy days♪

118
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,160
♪You understand my occasional timidity♪

119
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,880
♪When heavy rains fell♪

120
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,480
(Looks promising)
♪I suddenly realized♪

121
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:45,920
(Getting more and more confident)
♪Who can understand my rainy days♪

122
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,200
♪So I'm willing♪

123
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:50,200
♪To return to your side♪

124
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:50,920
Okay.

125
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,680
No problem.

126
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,000
It seems okay.

127
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,568
(Champagne already opened)
We won.

128
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,880
Although I don't know the song title,

129
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,200
